<b>Subject:</b> Excuse me?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1202" TARGET=_self>PVP Guild thoughts</A> (Raven De'Vine)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Just a thought.. as we all frequent this board already. What if

<BR>&gt; we all joined forces on the PVP server when the game goes
<BR>&gt; public.
<P>Are you implying everyone here should be friends with everyone else and that WE (the folks here) pick on those OTHERS that come into the PvP server? *grins* Well not a bad idea in a world where maybe no other Massively Multiplayer games already existed. You see, rivalries have ALREADY been created and enemies made. Although out of game many folks can tolerate each other AT BEST, in game many here will do nothing but try to kill each other because that is all they have done for years. It is part of the fun!
<P>In any case, the answer to your question, if that is what it is, is that with many folks here loyalties already exist with friends made as well as enemies.
<P>If you are interested in joining a guild there is a page on this site that has a PORTALS section you may want to check out leading to the various guilds or feel free to visit <a href="http://personal.lig.bellsouth.net/lig/g/r/grayrage/dbmain.htm"><font color="#800000"
<BR>size="7" face="Tempus Sans ITC"><b>... DarkenBane Company!</b></font></a>
<P>-Gray
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
